A. Very much, in questions concerning the nature of 
God, and concerning Uie estate of man's soul after death, 
in heaven, hell, and purgatory; by which you and every 
man know, how great obedience^ and how much money they 
gain from the common people. — Whereas Aristotle holdeth 
the soul of man to be the first gber of tnoHon to the body, 
