enemies, Fortltiide « ^ «>yl TiTfinti tivrt though k be 
necessaiy in such private men m shall be soIdien» yet^ for 
other men, the less they dare^ the better it is both for the 
commonwealth and for themselves. Frugality (t hough 
perhaps you will think it strange) is also a royal virtue : for 
it increases the public stock, which cannot be too great for 
the public use, nor any man too sparing of what he has in 
